column1: #Text=Polycrystalline samples of Sr2−xLaxCoNbO6 (x = 0–1)\rwere synthesized in a single phase by a solid-state route using\rstoichiometric amounts of SrCO3, Co3O4, Nb2O5, La2O3, and\rfinal sintering at 1300 oC; more details of preparation and\rcharacterization can be found in Ref. [39].

#Text=The temperatureand\rmagnetic-field-dependent heat capacity using relaxation\rtechnique (1.8–300 K and up to 9 T), dc-magnetic susceptibility\rin both zero-field-cooled (ZFC) and field-cooled warming\r(FCW) modes, ac-susceptibility measurements at different excitation\rfrequencies, and time-dependent magnetization [M(t)]\rin different protocols (i.e., TRM and aging effect) have been\rperformed using DynaCool Physical Property Measurement\rSystem from Quantum Design at KIT, Germany.
#Text=For more\rdetails of the protocol of different measurements, we refer to\rthe next section with their respective discussion.
